## Quick Conversion Cheat Sheet
```
PEM ←──────→ DER          (encoding flip)
PEM ───────→ PKCS#12      (bundle key+cert+chain)
PKCS#12 ───→ PEM          (extract components)
PKCS#7 ────→ PEM          (extract certs, no keys)
JKS ←──────→ PKCS#12      (via keytool)
                ↕
              PEM          (via openssl)


The golden rule for OpenShift: get everything into PEM, concatenate chains top-down (leaf → intermediate → root), and put them in Kubernetes TLS Secrets or ConfigMaps. If a Java app needs PKCS#12, convert from PEM as a build/init step or deliver the P12 via a generic Secret.
